WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:01:48.766 --> 00:01:52.645
It's been near six years since I
last saw my lord husband. Maester.

3
00:01:53.687 --> 00:01:56.648
I must know... will he live?

4
00:01:57.565 --> 00:02:00.068
He led his sailors into an ambush.

5
00:02:00.152 --> 00:02:04.030
A ship made to look
as if it were abandoned.

6
00:02:04.113 --> 00:02:08.743
In the fighting. his neck was slashed
by a corsair's dagger.

7
00:02:08.827 --> 00:02:11.205
He fell overboard into the sea.

8
00:02:11.288 --> 00:02:13.249
The wound was severe.

9
00:02:13.332 --> 00:02:14.958
Much blood was lost.

10
00:02:15.041 --> 00:02:18.045
But the greater concern
is the fever that followed.

11
00:02:18.128 --> 00:02:22.048
The ship's maester said
he burns from within.

12
00:02:34.395 --> 00:02:36.188
The ravens came in from?

13
00:02:36.271 --> 00:02:38.398
Even fall. Princess.

14
00:02:39.816 --> 00:02:41.944
So they arrive in three days.

15
00:02:44.321 --> 00:02:46.991
Let all be made ready to receive him.
Maester Kelvyn.

16
00:02:53.455 --> 00:02:55.624
The Sea Snake is strong.

17
00:02:55.708 --> 00:02:57.333
No doubt.

18
00:02:57.417 --> 00:03:01.463
And yet. I have seen blood fever
overcome men half his age.

19
00:03:01.546 --> 00:03:04.675
I will not suffer the talk
of crows in my house. Vaemond.

20
00:03:04.758 --> 00:03:07.343
I love my brother...

21
00:03:07.427 --> 00:03:10.096
but we must be honest with ourselves.

22
00:03:10.179 --> 00:03:12.266
We may greet his ship to find him gone.

23
00:03:12.349 --> 00:03:14.809
And who will take the Driftwood Throne?

24
00:03:14.893 --> 00:03:16.645
My grandmother seems
quite comfortable here.

25
00:03:16.729 --> 00:03:20.273
She presides only in the absence
of her husband.

26
00:03:21.024 --> 00:03:23.527
On his death. the seat passes.

27
00:03:23.611 --> 00:03:24.694
To Lucerys Velaryon.

28
00:03:24.778 --> 00:03:26.404
As is my lord husband's desire.

29
00:03:26.487 --> 00:03:29.950
I am the Sea Snake's own blood.

30
00:03:30.034 --> 00:03:32.535
the closest kin he has left.

31
00:03:32.619 --> 00:03:34.830
Be careful. good-brother.

32
00:03:34.914 --> 00:03:36.665
One could take your words for treason.

33
00:03:45.506 --> 00:03:48.427
I speak the truth. Rhaenys.

34
00:03:49.677 --> 00:03:51.012
And you know it.

35
00:03:52.264 --> 00:03:53.974
The matter has been decided.

36
00:03:54.057 --> 00:03:55.975
By a man whose ambition

37
00:03:56.059 --> 00:03:59.647
has brought down on us
calamity after calamity.

38
00:03:59.730 --> 00:04:02.857
My brother cares only
for the history books.

39
00:04:05.152 --> 00:04:07.320
But what of the Velaryon line?

40
00:04:07.403 --> 00:04:09.949
Is it to be snuffed out.

41
00:04:10.032 --> 00:04:13.159
supplanted by the pups of House Strong?

42
00:04:13.242 --> 00:04:16.829
Driftmark is mine by all rights.

43
00:04:16.913 --> 00:04:18.790
And while I should like your support.

44
00:04:18.874 --> 00:04:21.793
I do not... need it.

45
00:04:24.129 --> 00:04:26.047
The winds have shifted.

46
00:04:26.965 --> 00:04:31.345
The crown has good
reason to take my side.

47
00:04:31.427 --> 00:04:34.181
My cousin the King
would have your tongue for this.

48
00:04:34.264 --> 00:04:39.186
But it's not a king who sits
the Iron Throne these days. good-sister.

49
00:04:40.144 --> 00:04:41.689
It's a queen.

50
00:07:00.160 --> 00:07:03.872
The Conqueror and his sisters
sailed with a great army.

51
00:07:10.002 --> 00:07:13.297
And landed at the Blackwater Rush.

52
00:07:19.971 --> 00:07:21.430
At the end?

53
00:07:21.514 --> 00:07:25.059
- The mouth.
- Mouth! Come on. Jace. you knew that.

54
00:07:33.694 --> 00:07:34.735
Come on. Jace.

55
00:07:34.819 --> 00:07:36.379
Perhaps that's enough for this morning.

56
00:07:36.446 --> 00:07:38.447
No. no. I want to keep going.

57
00:07:39.867 --> 00:07:40.951
Maester.

58
00:07:44.413 --> 00:07:47.749
Aegon... ordered
that the trees should be...

59
00:07:48.833 --> 00:07:50.752
- killed.
- Felled.

60
00:07:50.836 --> 00:07:52.629
It is a related word.

61
00:07:52.713 --> 00:07:55.215
I don't expect you to learn
High Valyrian in a day. Jace.

62
00:07:55.298 --> 00:07:58.634
A king should honor the traditions
of his forbears.

63
00:07:58.718 --> 00:08:01.138
Well... unless you're planning

64
00:08:01.220 --> 00:08:04.182
to depose your own mother.
you have plenty of time to study.

65
00:08:12.607 --> 00:08:13.734
Leave us.

66
00:08:15.819 --> 00:08:17.571
Joffrey... come.

67
00:08:38.383 --> 00:08:41.720
He means to call into question
Luke's legitimacy.

68
00:08:42.553 --> 00:08:44.389
And by extension Jace.

69
00:08:44.472 --> 00:08:46.600
and by extension
my own claim to the throne.

70
00:08:46.682 --> 00:08:50.729
Vaemond cares only about Driftmark
and the Velaryon line.

71
00:08:50.812 --> 00:08:53.190
Not about our politics.

72
00:08:53.273 --> 00:08:55.399
Has he made common cause
with Otto High tower yet?

73
00:08:55.484 --> 00:08:57.277
This is what I fear.

74
00:08:57.360 --> 00:08:59.403
Rhaenys has flown to court.

75
00:08:59.488 --> 00:09:01.167
Surely. she cannot
be planning to back him.

76
00:09:01.240 --> 00:09:03.115
No. Whatever disagreements
we may have had.

77
00:09:03.200 --> 00:09:04.743
she's not cruel...

78
00:09:05.369 --> 00:09:08.080
- or stupid enough to do that.
- Disagreements?

79
00:09:08.163 --> 00:09:11.207
She believes we had her son killed
so that we might marry.

80
00:09:11.291 --> 00:09:15.086
Yes... and yet. she's
taken Baela to ward.

81
00:09:15.169 --> 00:09:17.880
Yes. It is Laena's memory she honors.
She has no love for us.

82
00:09:19.715 --> 00:09:21.927
Has the vipers' venom spread so far?

83
00:09:22.009 --> 00:09:25.180
Those vipers rule in my father's name.

84
00:09:25.264 --> 00:09:26.807
And my father...

85
00:09:33.772 --> 00:09:35.731
What choice do I have?

86
00:09:41.904 --> 00:09:43.824
To King's Landing. then.

87
00:10:24.531 --> 00:10:27.701
All hail Rhaenyra of House Targaryen.

88
00:10:27.783 --> 00:10:30.412
Princess of Dragons tone
and heir to the Iron Throne

89
00:10:30.494 --> 00:10:33.956
and her royal consort.
Prince Daemon Targaryen.

90
00:11:07.823 --> 00:11:09.951
Welcome back. Princess.

91
00:11:10.911 --> 00:11:12.037
Lord Caswell.

92
00:11:21.712 --> 00:11:24.715
I would say it's nice to be home.
but I scarcely recognize it.

93
00:11:30.514 --> 00:11:35.768
We have continued to enjoy
improved customs duties

94
00:11:35.851 --> 00:11:38.145
since the settling of the Step stones.

95
00:11:38.230 --> 00:11:41.233
And the extent to which we exploit those

96
00:11:41.316 --> 00:11:45.528
is contingent on
the harbor master's receipts.

97
00:11:45.611 --> 00:11:50.783
Of which septons have requested

98
00:11:50.866 --> 00:11:53.161
half that again for a bronze bust

99
00:11:53.244 --> 00:11:56.914
they wish to commission
for the Festival of the Mother.

100
00:11:56.998 --> 00:11:58.417
which I would not recommend.

101
00:11:58.499 --> 00:12:01.378
Thank you for that exhaustive
accounting. Lord Beesbury.

102
00:12:01.461 --> 00:12:02.546
I remind you...

103
00:12:10.177 --> 00:12:12.305
Your guests have arrived. Your Grace.

104
00:12:12.389 --> 00:12:15.182
I trust they've been welcomed
as befits their station.

105
00:12:15.267 --> 00:12:17.185
As you instructed. Lord Hand.

106
00:12:18.728 --> 00:12:22.691
It was my understanding Lord Corlys
wished for his grandson Lucerys

107
00:12:22.773 --> 00:12:24.526
to succeed him as Lord of the Tides.

108
00:12:24.609 --> 00:12:28.613
The boy has been raised most of his life
away from Driftmark.

109
00:12:28.696 --> 00:12:31.991
He can fly a dragon. yes.
but can he command a fleet?

110
00:12:32.075 --> 00:12:34.452
Ability does not alter his claim.

111
00:12:34.536 --> 00:12:37.496
The Sea Snake has never
formally named him as heir.

112
00:12:37.581 --> 00:12:38.956
if it comes to that.

113
00:12:39.039 --> 00:12:41.500
The crown must choose
what is best for the realm.

114
00:12:41.585 --> 00:12:44.336
He is Laenor's son.
What grounds could there be...

115
00:12:44.421 --> 00:12:46.465
What indeed. Lord Beesbury.

116
00:12:46.547 --> 00:12:48.090
What indeed.

117
00:12:49.259 --> 00:12:50.820
We shall hear
Princess Rhaenyra's petition.

118
00:12:50.844 --> 00:12:52.946
along with those of the other claimants
on the morrow.

119
00:12:52.970 --> 00:12:55.932
I do beg your pardon. my lords.

120
00:12:56.015 --> 00:12:57.350
I must greet our guests.

121
00:13:02.855 --> 00:13:05.649
Shall we levy a tax
on the sale of new wool?

122
00:13:05.734 --> 00:13:07.527
Your Grace...

123
00:13:07.610 --> 00:13:09.653
a matter has arisen that
requires your attention.

124
00:13:09.738 --> 00:13:11.865
Whatever it is. Ser Arryk.
it'll need to wait.

125
00:13:11.947 --> 00:13:15.659
- I'm Erryk. Your Grace.
- Of course. My apologies. ser.

126
00:13:15.744 --> 00:13:17.369
It's about the Prince.

127
00:13:17.453 --> 00:13:20.373
There's been a delicate situation
in his apartments.

128
00:13:51.988 --> 00:13:53.907
Father?

129
00:14:18.639 --> 00:14:21.393
- Who goes there?
- Father.

130
00:14:22.726 --> 00:14:25.272
It's me. my King.

131
00:14:26.230 --> 00:14:27.731
Rhaenyra.

132
00:14:29.609 --> 00:14:30.860
Oh...

133
00:14:35.740 --> 00:14:37.658
I'm here with Daemon.

134
00:14:38.326 --> 00:14:39.869
Daemon?

135
00:14:40.494 --> 00:14:41.620
Daemon?

136
00:14:44.124 --> 00:14:45.499
Daemon.

137
00:14:48.878 --> 00:14:50.212
Help me up.

138
00:14:56.595 --> 00:14:57.762
Oh...

139
00:15:07.522 --> 00:15:09.648
It has been so long.

140
00:15:15.196 --> 00:15:19.116
The Sea Snake has taken a grave
wound in battle in the Step stones.

141
00:15:20.619 --> 00:15:22.328
When?

142
00:15:22.412 --> 00:15:24.913
We won that war years ago.

143
00:15:24.998 --> 00:15:25.998
No.

144
00:15:27.292 --> 00:15:29.210
The Triarchy is resurgent.

145
00:15:30.544 --> 00:15:32.464
The fighting is anew.

146
00:15:34.173 --> 00:15:37.092
There is a petition to decide
upon the succession of Driftmark

147
00:15:37.177 --> 00:15:39.220
and the heir to the Driftwood Throne.

148
00:15:42.057 --> 00:15:44.058
Petitions?

149
00:15:45.851 --> 00:15:50.065
Alicent and Otto...
they see to all that business now.

150
00:15:50.148 --> 00:15:52.149
No. brother. listen to me.

151
00:15:53.067 --> 00:15:56.403
You are to affirm
your position for Lucerys

152
00:15:56.488 --> 00:15:58.990
to be Corlys Velaryon's successor.

153
00:16:01.033 --> 00:16:03.912
Has something happened to Lord Corlys?

154
00:16:05.788 --> 00:16:06.914
Father...

155
00:16:07.666 --> 00:16:10.585
there's someone we wish
to introduce you to.

156
00:16:28.394 --> 00:16:29.770
Daemon.

157
00:16:31.773 --> 00:16:32.941
Brother.

158
00:16:35.777 --> 00:16:37.320
Who is that?

159
00:16:39.029 --> 00:16:40.572
Father...

160
00:16:41.865 --> 00:16:44.411
this is Aegon.

161
00:16:45.244 --> 00:16:47.413
Aegon.

162
00:16:47.496 --> 00:16:50.417
And this... is Viserys.

163
00:16:52.418 --> 00:16:55.754
Ah... Viserys.

164
00:16:59.216 --> 00:17:03.595
Now that is a name fit for a king.

165
00:17:07.642 --> 00:17:09.102
Oh...

166
00:17:11.479 --> 00:17:14.441
Oh. oh...

167
00:17:14.524 --> 00:17:15.607
Oh. I'm sorry.

168
00:17:16.526 --> 00:17:19.695
Oh. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

169
00:17:19.778 --> 00:17:21.364
I'm so...

170
00:17:24.826 --> 00:17:27.620
I'm sorry. I'm sor...

171
00:17:27.703 --> 00:17:28.788
Please.

172
00:17:30.289 --> 00:17:33.876
- My tea. My tea.
- What tea? This?

173
00:17:33.960 --> 00:17:36.378
Yes. Yes.

174
00:17:37.797 --> 00:17:39.047
Yes.

175
00:18:07.701 --> 00:18:10.288
I brought her here immediately.

176
00:18:10.371 --> 00:18:12.289
She's seen no one else. Your Grace.

177
00:18:17.336 --> 00:18:19.255
Come here. sweetling.

178
00:18:28.847 --> 00:18:30.098
Tell me your name.

179
00:18:33.603 --> 00:18:35.395
It's Dyana. Your Grace.

180
00:18:37.816 --> 00:18:39.150
If it please you.

181
00:18:40.902 --> 00:18:44.029
Dyana. What a pretty name.

182
00:18:46.990 --> 00:18:49.117
I understand you've found
yourself in some trouble.

183
00:18:52.788 --> 00:18:54.582
I was fetching the Prince his wine.

184
00:18:54.665 --> 00:18:58.586
and I put it on his table.
and when I turned...

185
00:18:59.586 --> 00:19:01.130
I didn't see him.

186
00:19:02.172 --> 00:19:04.342
I asked him to stop. Your Grace.

187
00:19:04.424 --> 00:19:07.178
I did. truly...

188
00:19:07.261 --> 00:19:09.137
you must believe me.

189
00:19:23.236 --> 00:19:25.153
Thank you for telling me. Dyana.

190
00:19:30.410 --> 00:19:32.537
I know it wasn't your fault.

191
00:19:34.788 --> 00:19:36.624
I believe you.

192
00:19:36.708 --> 00:19:38.250
You do?

193
00:19:39.501 --> 00:19:40.627
I do.

194
00:19:43.797 --> 00:19:45.717
But what I worry about...

195
00:19:46.968 --> 00:19:48.886
is what others might believe.

196
00:19:50.971 --> 00:19:53.348
You were alone with the Prince.
were you not?

197
00:19:53.432 --> 00:19:55.684
Yes. I...

198
00:19:55.768 --> 00:19:58.520
And no one else saw what happened
between the two of you.

199
00:19:59.439 --> 00:20:01.607
If anyone else were
to hear about this...

200
00:20:01.691 --> 00:20:05.819
- I haven't told anyone.
- You told Ser Erryk and Talya and now me.

201
00:20:06.778 --> 00:20:10.074
And though I believe you are not to
blame. others might not be so trusting.

202
00:20:11.659 --> 00:20:14.578
They might think you were trying
to besmirch the Prince. or worse...

203
00:20:15.579 --> 00:20:18.579
that you're the sort of girl that might
have enticed him in the first place.

204
00:20:20.293 --> 00:20:22.420
And you know what happens
to girls like that.

205
00:20:24.463 --> 00:20:29.009
I wouldn't dream of breathing
another word to anyone. Your Grace.

206
00:20:30.135 --> 00:20:32.430
I swear it on my life.

207
00:20:39.812 --> 00:20:41.355
I know you won't.

208
00:20:54.242 --> 00:20:55.745
For your troubles.

209
00:21:03.336 --> 00:21:05.253
The tea. Your Grace.

210
00:21:19.768 --> 00:21:20.936
It's best to be certain.

211
00:21:48.797 --> 00:21:50.298
Get up.

212
00:21:50.383 --> 00:21:51.925
Aegon!

213
00:21:54.761 --> 00:21:55.887
Get up!

214
00:21:59.517 --> 00:22:00.518
Mother?

215
00:22:02.144 --> 00:22:05.731
- What is it?
- "What is it? What is it?

216
00:22:05.815 --> 00:22:07.584
What is it?"
That's all you can say for yourself?

217
00:22:07.607 --> 00:22:08.942
Has something happened?

218
00:22:10.068 --> 00:22:11.237
Dyana.

219
00:22:12.697 --> 00:22:14.240
The serving girl.

220
00:22:15.115 --> 00:22:18.076
Oh. for the gods' sake.

221
00:22:18.161 --> 00:22:20.579
The girl. Aegon. The one
you sent fleeing from your company.

222
00:22:20.663 --> 00:22:23.290
It was just harmless fun.

223
00:22:23.374 --> 00:22:26.794
She didn't need to go
and get upset about it.

224
00:22:26.877 --> 00:22:30.213
Think of the shame on your wife. on me.

225
00:22:31.257 --> 00:22:33.509
How can you keep carrying on like this.

226
00:22:33.593 --> 00:22:35.470
especially on a day like today?

227
00:22:35.553 --> 00:22:37.055
Why? What is it today?

228
00:22:52.028 --> 00:22:53.779
You are no son of mine.

229
00:22:59.786 --> 00:23:02.079
I did not ask for this.

230
00:23:02.163 --> 00:23:04.164
I've done everything you've asked me to.

231
00:23:04.248 --> 00:23:06.334
and I try so...

232
00:23:06.416 --> 00:23:09.586
I try so hard. but it will never
be enough for you or father.

233
00:23:12.131 --> 00:23:16.009
Have you seen Dyana?
She's supposed to dress the children.

234
00:23:23.433 --> 00:23:26.394
He looks like a different person.

235
00:23:26.479 --> 00:23:30.066
I believe we should also
consult Maester Gerardys.

236
00:23:30.149 --> 00:23:32.984
Perhaps if he could see the King.
he'd suggest a different...

237
00:23:33.068 --> 00:23:35.113
Princess Rhaenyra.

238
00:23:35.195 --> 00:23:36.739
And Prince Daemon.

239
00:23:39.241 --> 00:23:42.577
It has been so long since we were
granted the joy of your presence.

240
00:23:45.455 --> 00:23:47.040
Indeed. Your Grace.

241
00:23:47.124 --> 00:23:50.044
Though not long enough to
merit a greeting upon our arrival.

242
00:23:50.627 --> 00:23:53.338
I'm sure the Queen had
pressing business. my love.

243
00:23:54.422 --> 00:23:56.800
What can either of us
know of ruling a kingdom?

244
00:23:56.884 --> 00:23:59.595
I do not rule. as you well know.

245
00:23:59.679 --> 00:24:02.306
My father and I are mere
stewards of the King's will and wisdom.

246
00:24:02.390 --> 00:24:04.599
And how exactly is
that wisdom expressed?

247
00:24:06.893 --> 00:24:08.980
In blinks and wheezes?

248
00:24:09.063 --> 00:24:10.790
I'd be surprised if he could remember
his own name.

249
00:24:10.815 --> 00:24:12.650
- Or if you could.
- King Viserys's condition

250
00:24:12.732 --> 00:24:14.317
has worsened since you saw him last.

251
00:24:16.194 --> 00:24:17.989
It subjects him to considerable pain.

252
00:24:18.072 --> 00:24:20.575
- On the advice of the maesters...
- Ah. the maesters.

253
00:24:20.657 --> 00:24:23.661
Of course. It is they who keep him...

254
00:24:24.245 --> 00:24:27.914
addled on milk of the poppy
while the High towers warm his throne.

255
00:24:27.999 --> 00:24:31.711
Rhaenyra. if you would see him
without it. almost blind with suffering.

256
00:24:31.794 --> 00:24:35.631
Alicent. I have no doubt
it was an act of the purest mercy.

257
00:24:35.714 --> 00:24:38.175
but tell me. for the King's suffering.

258
00:24:38.259 --> 00:24:41.261
did the maesters also prescribe
the removal of Targaryen heraldry

259
00:24:41.345 --> 00:24:43.931
and the installation in its stead
of various statues and stars?

260
00:24:45.182 --> 00:24:48.477
The emblems of the Seven serve only
to guide us on an uncertain path.

261
00:24:48.560 --> 00:24:51.355
- To remind us of a higher authority.
- And on the morrow.

262
00:24:51.439 --> 00:24:55.108
which authority will sit in judgment of
my son's claim on his own inheritance?

263
00:24:56.027 --> 00:24:58.738
That would be mine... and the Hand's.

264
00:24:58.820 --> 00:25:00.780
But be assured.
the Father is just and commands me

265
00:25:00.865 --> 00:25:03.992
to forget the accusations
you have hurled in this room today.

266
00:25:10.208 --> 00:25:13.794
- Smaller than I remember.
- It looks exactly the same.

267
00:25:13.877 --> 00:25:15.337
Luke. come on.

268
00:25:30.894 --> 00:25:33.439
See? I told you this
would still be here.

269
00:25:33.521 --> 00:25:36.107
And you thought you could swing
Criston's morning star.

270
00:25:36.858 --> 00:25:38.778
And you almost took your own head off.

271
00:25:44.325 --> 00:25:47.036
- What's your problem?
- Everyone's staring at us.

272
00:25:50.373 --> 00:25:53.291
No one would question me
being heir to Driftmark...

273
00:25:54.125 --> 00:25:55.252
if...

274
00:25:56.170 --> 00:25:59.882
if I looked more like Ser Laenor
Velaryon than Ser Harwin Strong.

275
00:26:01.509 --> 00:26:03.844
It doesn't matter what they think.

276
00:26:48.638 --> 00:26:50.141
Well done. my Prince.

277
00:26:50.223 --> 00:26:51.701
You'll be winning tourneys in no time.

278
00:26:51.726 --> 00:26:53.853
I don't give a shit about tourneys.

279
00:26:54.644 --> 00:26:55.770
Nephews...

280
00:26:57.315 --> 00:26:58.481
have you come to train?

281
00:26:59.566 --> 00:27:00.901
Open the gate!

282
00:27:34.977 --> 00:27:36.770
Hold your nerve. my Queen.

283
00:27:36.854 --> 00:27:39.272
What we do.
we do for the good of the realm.

284
00:27:39.356 --> 00:27:43.193
I must confess a certain uneasiness
now this is at hand.

285
00:27:44.194 --> 00:27:48.324
- He may yet live.
- But we must be prepared if he does not.

286
00:27:56.790 --> 00:27:59.585
The realm has enjoyed a long peace.

287
00:27:59.668 --> 00:28:02.630
a credit to the work of both
Jaehaerys and Viserys.

288
00:28:02.712 --> 00:28:06.342
but the threat of war looms
and may arrive on our shores.

289
00:28:06.424 --> 00:28:09.511
When it does.
will you want a child at the command

290
00:28:09.595 --> 00:28:11.721
of the greatest fleet in Westeros?

291
00:28:13.557 --> 00:28:15.476
We must. of course...

292
00:28:16.602 --> 00:28:18.729
act in the interest of our subjects.

293
00:28:20.772 --> 00:28:24.317
The next Lord of the Tides
will be deeply in your debt. Your Grace.

294
00:28:25.277 --> 00:28:26.653
As will Driftmark...

295
00:28:26.737 --> 00:28:28.823
in all its strength.

296
00:28:46.172 --> 00:28:47.716
Grandmother?

297
00:28:51.470 --> 00:28:52.470
Rhaena.

298
00:29:00.438 --> 00:29:02.565
Baela said you might be here.

299
00:29:04.400 --> 00:29:06.109
She's done well as your ward.

300
00:29:06.192 --> 00:29:07.318
You've...

301
00:29:08.778 --> 00:29:10.155
raised her admirably.

302
00:29:10.239 --> 00:29:12.657
You honor me. Princess.

303
00:29:13.784 --> 00:29:16.327
Might I speak to the Princess alone.
Rhaena?

304
00:29:19.707 --> 00:29:20.833
Princess.

305
00:29:30.675 --> 00:29:36.222
I wondered for many an hour
what your purpose was in coming here.

306
00:29:36.307 --> 00:29:39.351
Whether you'd speak for or against
the suit brought by Ser Vaemond.

307
00:29:39.434 --> 00:29:41.353
But then. I realized...

308
00:29:42.229 --> 00:29:44.147
you intend to advocate for yourself.

309
00:29:47.609 --> 00:29:50.195
This is no fair proceeding.

310
00:29:50.278 --> 00:29:54.240
It is a trap set by the Queen
and the Hand. I'd wager.

311
00:29:54.325 --> 00:29:56.160
to proclaim my son illegitimate.

312
00:29:56.242 --> 00:29:59.163
Yet you did worse than that with Laenor.

313
00:30:01.332 --> 00:30:02.458
Did you not?

314
00:30:08.881 --> 00:30:10.466
I loved your son.

315
00:30:12.926 --> 00:30:15.845
You may not believe it
to be true. but I did.

316
00:30:19.642 --> 00:30:22.560
I did not order his death.

317
00:30:24.230 --> 00:30:27.149
Nor was I complicit in it.
I swear this to you.

318
00:30:34.615 --> 00:30:36.032
I'll make you an offer.

319
00:30:39.620 --> 00:30:40.828
Back Luke's claim.

320
00:30:40.913 --> 00:30:43.457
and let us betroth
Laena's children to mine.

321
00:30:45.500 --> 00:30:50.088
Baela will be Queen
of the Seven Kingdoms

322
00:30:50.172 --> 00:30:52.883
and her sons will be
heirs to the throne.

323
00:30:52.967 --> 00:30:55.928
Rhaena will rule in Driftmark. and

324
00:30:56.010 --> 00:30:58.556
the seat will pass to her and Lucerys's
children in time.

325
00:30:59.265 --> 00:31:00.766
A generous offer.

326
00:31:02.977 --> 00:31:05.895
- Or a desperate one.
- What does it matter?

327
00:31:10.483 --> 00:31:12.403
You are right in this. at least.

328
00:31:16.781 --> 00:31:18.116
It does not matter.

329
00:31:28.626 --> 00:31:30.962
You can bargain with me all you like.

330
00:31:31.880 --> 00:31:34.424
Bring my granddaughter
with you to soften my resolve.

331
00:31:36.134 --> 00:31:39.680
But tomorrow.
the High towers land their first blow.

332
00:31:41.181 --> 00:31:43.517
They force you to your knees...

333
00:31:44.309 --> 00:31:46.228
and I must stand alone.

334
00:32:29.688 --> 00:32:31.065
Alicent?

335
00:32:32.441 --> 00:32:33.941
Alicent...

336
00:32:34.026 --> 00:32:36.028
No. it's Rhaenyra. father.

337
00:32:40.365 --> 00:32:41.700
Rhaenyra.

338
00:32:47.914 --> 00:32:51.250
"The Song of Ice and Fire."
Do you believe it to be true?

339
00:32:54.003 --> 00:32:55.922
Aegon's Dream.

340
00:32:59.843 --> 00:33:01.470
You told me

341
00:33:01.553 --> 00:33:05.473
it was our duty to hold
the realm united against a common foe.

342
00:33:09.603 --> 00:33:12.522
By naming me heir.
you divided the realm.

343
00:33:22.782 --> 00:33:24.701
I thought I wanted it.

344
00:33:34.836 --> 00:33:36.963
But the burden is a heavy one.

345
00:33:39.549 --> 00:33:41.468
It's too heavy.

346
00:33:49.101 --> 00:33:50.227
My...

347
00:33:51.854 --> 00:33:53.855
My only child.

348
00:33:58.277 --> 00:34:01.195
If you wish me to
bear it. then defend me.

349
00:34:02.740 --> 00:34:04.240
And my children.

350
00:34:08.120 --> 00:34:09.162
It's...

351
00:35:05.843 --> 00:35:07.971
I want to have supper. Otto.

352
00:35:10.640 --> 00:35:14.185
- It is the morning. Your Grace.
- Tonight.

353
00:35:17.147 --> 00:35:19.857
The whole of my family

354
00:35:19.942 --> 00:35:21.859
are gathered at the Red Keep.

355
00:35:24.363 --> 00:35:27.783
I want us... to dine together.

356
00:35:58.855 --> 00:36:00.774
Bring milk of the poppy.

357
00:36:15.162 --> 00:36:16.330
No.

358
00:36:19.584 --> 00:36:21.419
Just arrange the supper.

359
00:36:26.716 --> 00:36:28.593
Though it is the
great hope of this court

360
00:36:28.676 --> 00:36:33.055
that Lord Corlys Velaryon
survive his wounds.

361
00:36:33.140 --> 00:36:35.517
we gather here with the grim task

362
00:36:35.600 --> 00:36:38.145
of dealing with
the succession of Driftmark.

363
00:36:39.395 --> 00:36:42.566
As Hand. I speak with
the King's voice on this

364
00:36:42.649 --> 00:36:44.192
and all other matters.

365
00:36:46.569 --> 00:36:48.488
The crown will now hear the petitions.

366
00:36:49.656 --> 00:36:51.575
Ser Vaemond of House Velaryon.

367
00:36:59.917 --> 00:37:01.042
My Queen.

368
00:37:02.502 --> 00:37:03.629
My Lord Hand.

369
00:37:04.921 --> 00:37:08.008
The history of our noble houses
extends beyond the Seven Kingdoms

370
00:37:08.091 --> 00:37:10.301
to the days of Old Valyria.

371
00:37:10.384 --> 00:37:13.180
For as long as House Targaryen
has ruled the skies.

372
00:37:13.263 --> 00:37:15.890
House Velaryon has ruled the seas.

373
00:37:15.973 --> 00:37:20.479
When the Doom fell on Valyria. our
houses became the last of their kind.

374
00:37:20.562 --> 00:37:23.899
Our forebearers came to this new land.
knowing that were they to fail.

375
00:37:23.982 --> 00:37:27.109
it would mean the end to
their bloodlines and their name.

376
00:37:28.694 --> 00:37:32.448
I have spent my entire life on
Driftmark defending my brother's seat.

377
00:37:32.531 --> 00:37:36.243
I am Lord Corlys's closest kin.
his own blood.

378
00:37:36.328 --> 00:37:40.457
The true. unimpeachable blood
of House Velaryon runs through my veins.

379
00:37:40.540 --> 00:37:44.544
As it does in my sons.
the offspring of Laenor Velaryon.

380
00:37:44.627 --> 00:37:47.421
If you cared so much
about your house's blood. Ser Vaemond.

381
00:37:47.506 --> 00:37:49.692
you would not be so bold as
to supplant its rightful heir.

382
00:37:49.716 --> 00:37:53.095
No. you only speak for yourself
and for your own ambition.

383
00:37:53.178 --> 00:37:55.740
You will have chance to make
your own petition. Princess Rhaenyra.

384
00:37:55.763 --> 00:37:58.350
Do Ser Vaemond the courtesy
of allowing his to be heard.

385
00:38:04.314 --> 00:38:06.857
What do you know of Velaryon blood.
Princess?

386
00:38:08.317 --> 00:38:11.321
I could cut my veins and show it to you

387
00:38:11.404 --> 00:38:14.616
and you still wouldn't recognize it.

388
00:38:14.700 --> 00:38:18.620
This is about the future
and survival of my house. not yours.

389
00:38:23.750 --> 00:38:25.877
My Queen. my Lord Hand.

390
00:38:27.212 --> 00:38:30.131
This is a matter of blood. not ambition.

391
00:38:31.466 --> 00:38:36.263
I place the continuation of the survival
of my house and my line above all.

392
00:38:36.346 --> 00:38:39.473
I humbly put myself before you
as my brother's successor...

393
00:38:40.683 --> 00:38:44.229
the Lord of Driftmark
and Lord of the Tides.

394
00:38:45.312 --> 00:38:46.857
Thank you. Ser Vaemond.

395
00:38:53.988 --> 00:38:59.410
Princess Rhaenyra. you may now speak
for your son. Lucerys Velaryon.

396
00:39:04.832 --> 00:39:07.502
If I am to grace this farce
with some answer.

397
00:39:07.586 --> 00:39:11.131
I will start by reminding the court that
nearly 20 years ago. in this very...

398
00:39:16.470 --> 00:39:19.430
King Viserys of House Targaryen.

399
00:39:19.513 --> 00:39:21.515
the First of His Name.

400
00:39:21.600 --> 00:39:24.770
King of the Andals. and the Rhoynar.

401
00:39:24.852 --> 00:39:26.979
and the First Men.

402
00:39:27.064 --> 00:39:31.609
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms.
and Protector of the Realm.

403
00:40:51.522 --> 00:40:53.441
I will sit the throne today.

404
00:40:55.317 --> 00:40:56.653
Your Grace.

405
00:41:03.868 --> 00:41:06.745
I will be fine. I will be fine.

406
00:41:20.509 --> 00:41:22.428
I said I'm fine.

407
00:41:25.765 --> 00:41:26.933
- Ah...
- Come on.

408
00:41:34.274 --> 00:41:35.357
Steady.

409
00:42:17.067 --> 00:42:22.613
I must... admit... my confusion.

410
00:42:24.241 --> 00:42:26.493
I do not understand

411
00:42:26.575 --> 00:42:30.913
why petitions are being heard
over a settled succession.

412
00:42:30.997 --> 00:42:32.457
The only one present...

413
00:42:33.375 --> 00:42:37.962
who might offer keener insight
into Lord Corlys's wishes

414
00:42:38.046 --> 00:42:39.797
is the Princess Rhaenys.

415
00:42:43.593 --> 00:42:45.136
Indeed. Your Grace.

416
00:42:59.067 --> 00:43:02.194
It was ever my husband's
will that Driftmark

417
00:43:02.279 --> 00:43:04.948
pass through Ser Laenor

418
00:43:05.031 --> 00:43:06.950
to his true born son...

419
00:43:07.783 --> 00:43:09.868
Lucerys Velaryon.

420
00:43:09.953 --> 00:43:11.870
His mind never changed.

421
00:43:12.705 --> 00:43:14.874
Nor did my support of him.

422
00:43:16.000 --> 00:43:19.169
As a matter of fact. the Princess Rhaenyra
has just informed me of her desire

423
00:43:19.254 --> 00:43:21.381
to marry her sons Jace and Luke

424
00:43:21.464 --> 00:43:24.383
to Lord Corlys's granddaughters.
Baela and Rhaena.

425
00:43:25.259 --> 00:43:29.180
A proposal to which I heartily agree.

426
00:43:30.348 --> 00:43:33.892
Well... the matter is settled.

427
00:43:35.227 --> 00:43:36.562
Again.

428
00:43:37.730 --> 00:43:43.028
I hereby reaffirm
Prince Lucerys of House Velaryon

429
00:43:43.111 --> 00:43:45.279
as heir to Driftmark.

430
00:43:45.363 --> 00:43:50.243
the Driftwood Throne.
and the next Lord of the Tides.

431
00:43:56.750 --> 00:43:58.292
You break law...

432
00:43:59.544 --> 00:44:02.171
and centuries of tradition

433
00:44:02.254 --> 00:44:04.381
to install your daughter as heir.

434
00:44:05.591 --> 00:44:07.218
Yet you dare tell me...

435
00:44:08.261 --> 00:44:11.180
who deserves to inherit
the name Velaryon.

436
00:44:13.515 --> 00:44:14.515
No.

437
00:44:15.935 --> 00:44:18.187
I will not allow it.

438
00:44:19.064 --> 00:44:20.607
"Allow it"?

439
00:44:21.649 --> 00:44:23.817
Do not forget yourself. Vaemond.

440
00:44:27.696 --> 00:44:32.368
That is no true Velaryon.

441
00:44:32.451 --> 00:44:35.872
and certainly no nephew of mine.

442
00:44:35.955 --> 00:44:37.999
Go to your chambers.
You have said enough.

443
00:44:39.250 --> 00:44:42.796
Lucerys is my true-born grandson.

444
00:44:43.712 --> 00:44:45.297
And you...

445
00:44:45.381 --> 00:44:48.801
are no more
than the second son of Driftmark.

446
00:44:49.886 --> 00:44:54.808
You... may run your house
as you see fit...

447
00:44:55.558 --> 00:44:58.685
but you will not decide
the future of mine.

448
00:45:00.562 --> 00:45:02.816
My house survived the Doom

449
00:45:02.899 --> 00:45:05.609
and a thousand tribulations besides.

450
00:45:05.692 --> 00:45:07.611
And gods be damned...

451
00:45:08.904 --> 00:45:14.576
I will not see it ended
on the account of this...

452
00:45:16.162 --> 00:45:17.705
Say it.

453
00:45:28.299 --> 00:45:29.843
Her children...

454
00:45:30.551 --> 00:45:32.761
are bastards!

455
00:45:36.057 --> 00:45:37.350
And she...

456
00:45:38.350 --> 00:45:39.350
is...

457
00:45:40.185 --> 00:45:41.479
a whore.

458
00:45:48.153 --> 00:45:49.153
I...

459
00:45:50.863 --> 00:45:52.448
will have your tongue for that.

460
00:46:00.038 --> 00:46:02.292
He can keep his tongue.

461
00:46:02.375 --> 00:46:04.919
- Disarm him!
- No need.

462
00:46:12.551 --> 00:46:14.721
- Call the maesters!
- Father?

463
00:46:14.803 --> 00:46:17.723
Please. my love. You must
take something for the pain.

464
00:46:18.600 --> 00:46:21.185
I will not cloud my mind.

465
00:46:21.268 --> 00:46:23.604
I must put things right.

466
00:47:08.857 --> 00:47:13.404
The body will be ready for its return
to Driftmark on the morrow. my lady.

467
00:47:16.156 --> 00:47:20.160
You may wish to leave the Silent Sisters
to their work.

468
00:47:20.245 --> 00:47:22.788
It is ill luck to look
upon the face of death.

469
00:47:27.125 --> 00:47:31.672
The Stranger has visited me more times
than I can count. Grand Maester.

470
00:47:35.968 --> 00:47:37.511
I assure you...

471
00:47:38.638 --> 00:47:42.558
he cares little whether my eyes
are open or closed.

472
00:49:07.935 --> 00:49:11.272
How good it is...
to see you all tonight...

473
00:49:12.482 --> 00:49:13.607
together.

474
00:49:19.738 --> 00:49:22.325
- Prayer before we begin?
- Yes.

475
00:49:23.700 --> 00:49:26.120
May the Mother smile down
on this gathering with love.

476
00:49:27.080 --> 00:49:30.707
May the Smith mend the bonds
that have been broken for far too long.

477
00:49:30.792 --> 00:49:34.712
And to Vaemond Velaryon.
may the gods give him rest.

478
00:49:42.136 --> 00:49:45.932
This is an occasion for celebration.
it seems.

479
00:49:46.015 --> 00:49:48.433
My grandsons. Jace and Luke.

480
00:49:48.517 --> 00:49:51.770
will marry their cousins.
Baela and Rhaena.

481
00:49:51.854 --> 00:49:55.149
further strengthening the bond
between our houses.

482
00:49:55.232 --> 00:49:58.694
A toast to the young Princes...

483
00:49:58.778 --> 00:50:01.446
- and their betrothed.
- Hear. hear!

484
00:50:02.281 --> 00:50:04.825
Well done. Jace.
You'll finally get to lie with a woman.

485
00:50:05.910 --> 00:50:09.455
Let us toast as well Prince Lucerys...

486
00:50:10.288 --> 00:50:13.084
the future Lord of the Tides.

487
00:50:13.167 --> 00:50:14.459
Hear. hear.

488
00:50:14.544 --> 00:50:16.087
You'll be great.

489
00:50:19.674 --> 00:50:24.053
You do know how the
act is done. I assume?

490
00:50:24.136 --> 00:50:25.303
At least in principle?

491
00:50:25.388 --> 00:50:26.848
Where to put your cock and all that.

492
00:50:26.930 --> 00:50:28.265
Let it be. cousin.

493
00:50:28.348 --> 00:50:32.227
You can play the jester if you wish. but
hold your tongue before my betrothed.

494
00:50:53.707 --> 00:50:58.129
It both gladdens my heart

495
00:50:58.212 --> 00:51:02.383
and fills me with sorrow

496
00:51:02.466 --> 00:51:05.595
to see these faces around the table.

497
00:51:07.013 --> 00:51:10.558
The faces most dear
to me in all the world...

498
00:51:12.142 --> 00:51:14.352
yet grown so distant from each other...

499
00:51:15.479 --> 00:51:17.397
in the years past.

500
00:51:41.339 --> 00:51:43.883
My own face...

501
00:51:43.966 --> 00:51:46.218
is no longer a handsome one...

502
00:51:48.971 --> 00:51:50.890
if indeed it ever was.

503
00:51:54.100 --> 00:51:55.435
But tonight...

504
00:51:56.270 --> 00:51:59.607
I wish you to see me... as I am.

505
00:52:01.067 --> 00:52:02.609
Not just a king...

506
00:52:04.319 --> 00:52:05.904
but your father.

507
00:52:07.240 --> 00:52:08.491
Your brother.

508
00:52:09.200 --> 00:52:10.743
Your husband...

509
00:52:13.162 --> 00:52:14.705
and your grand sire.

510
00:52:15.872 --> 00:52:18.042
Who may not. it seems...

511
00:52:19.042 --> 00:52:20.962
walk for much longer among you.

512
00:52:26.676 --> 00:52:31.263
Let us no longer hold
ill feelings in our hearts.

513
00:52:32.473 --> 00:52:34.183
The crown cannot stand strong

514
00:52:34.267 --> 00:52:36.810
if the House of the Dragon
remains divided.

515
00:52:37.854 --> 00:52:40.605
But set aside your grievances.

516
00:52:44.109 --> 00:52:46.236
If not for the sake of the crown...

517
00:52:47.321 --> 00:52:49.448
then for the sake of this old man

518
00:52:50.448 --> 00:52:52.951
who loves you all

519
00:52:53.035 --> 00:52:54.578
so dearly.

520
00:53:21.564 --> 00:53:24.609
I wish to raise my cup
to Her Grace. the Queen.

521
00:53:28.738 --> 00:53:30.488
I love my father.

522
00:53:31.198 --> 00:53:33.743
But I must admit that
no one has stood...

523
00:53:34.660 --> 00:53:37.162
more loyally by his side
than his good wife.

524
00:53:40.415 --> 00:53:42.334
She has tended to him with...

525
00:53:43.419 --> 00:53:45.587
unfailing devotion.

526
00:53:45.671 --> 00:53:48.214
love. and honor.

527
00:53:49.591 --> 00:53:52.136
And for that. she has my gratitude...

528
00:53:54.013 --> 00:53:55.555
and my apology.

529
00:54:04.857 --> 00:54:07.734
Your graciousness moves me deeply.
Princess.

530
00:54:11.113 --> 00:54:12.865
We are both mothers...

531
00:54:15.368 --> 00:54:17.285
and we love our children.

532
00:54:20.665 --> 00:54:23.584
We have more in common
than we sometimes allow.

533
00:54:26.796 --> 00:54:30.341
I raise my cup to you and to your house.

534
00:54:35.388 --> 00:54:37.390
You will make a fine queen.

535
00:55:13.341 --> 00:55:14.468
I...

536
00:55:15.553 --> 00:55:18.096
I regret the disappointment
you are soon to suffer.

537
00:55:19.015 --> 00:55:22.435
But if you ever wish to know
what it is to be well satisfied.

538
00:55:22.517 --> 00:55:24.602
all you have to do is ask.

539
00:55:25.270 --> 00:55:26.270
Jace.

540
00:55:55.008 --> 00:55:59.180
To Prince Aegon and Prince Aemond.

541
00:55:59.263 --> 00:56:02.558
We have not seen each other in years.

542
00:56:02.640 --> 00:56:05.393
but I have fond memories
of our shared youth.

543
00:56:07.812 --> 00:56:11.734
And as men. I hope we may
yet be friends and allies.

544
00:56:12.859 --> 00:56:15.404
To you and your family's
good health. dear uncles.

545
00:56:23.328 --> 00:56:24.622
To you as well.

546
00:56:32.296 --> 00:56:34.714
Beware the beast beneath the boards.

547
00:56:34.799 --> 00:56:36.216
Well done. my boy.

548
00:56:36.299 --> 00:56:39.053
I would like to toast
to Baela and Rhaena.

549
00:56:39.678 --> 00:56:41.596
They'll be married soon.

550
00:56:42.765 --> 00:56:45.892
It isn't so bad.
Mostly he just ignores you...

551
00:56:47.143 --> 00:56:49.020
except sometimes when he's drunk.

552
00:56:57.571 --> 00:57:00.866
- Good.
- Let us have some music.

553
00:57:06.205 --> 00:57:07.455
Excuse me.

554
00:58:39.214 --> 00:58:41.758
Guards.

555
00:58:49.015 --> 00:58:50.308
Please. sit down.

556
00:59:29.890 --> 00:59:31.225
Final tribute.

557
00:59:34.310 --> 00:59:36.229
To the health of my nephews:

558
00:59:37.189 --> 00:59:38.274
Jace...

559
00:59:39.817 --> 00:59:40.984
Luke...

560
00:59:42.069 --> 00:59:43.194
and Joffrey.

561
00:59:44.696 --> 00:59:48.033
Each of them handsome. wise...

562
00:59:55.290 --> 00:59:56.709
- strong.
- Aemond.

563
00:59:56.792 --> 00:59:57.917
Come...

564
00:59:59.669 --> 01:00:03.214
let us drain our cups to these three...

565
01:00:03.966 --> 01:00:06.134
- Strong boys.
- I dare you to say that again.

566
01:00:06.218 --> 01:00:09.305
Why? 'Twas only a compliment.

567
01:00:09.388 --> 01:00:10.763
Do you not think yourself Strong?

568
01:00:11.640 --> 01:00:13.683
- Jace!
- That is enough!

569
01:00:20.607 --> 01:00:22.609
Why would you say such a thing
before these people?

570
01:00:22.692 --> 01:00:25.863
I was merely expressing how proud I am
of my family. Mother.

571
01:00:25.946 --> 01:00:29.700
Mm. though it seems my nephews
aren't quite as proud of theirs.

572
01:00:29.783 --> 01:00:31.701
Wait. wait!

573
01:00:35.288 --> 01:00:38.417
Go to your quarters.
All of you go. now.

574
01:00:57.227 --> 01:00:58.354
Rhaenyra.

575
01:01:02.816 --> 01:01:05.444
It's best. I think.
if we go back to Dragons tone.

576
01:01:05.526 --> 01:01:07.446
You've only just arrived.

577
01:01:13.535 --> 01:01:15.453
Let me see the children home.

578
01:01:16.330 --> 01:01:17.663
I'll...

579
01:01:19.082 --> 01:01:20.834
return on dragon back.

580
01:01:25.214 --> 01:01:27.131
The King and I would both like that.

581
01:02:08.966 --> 01:02:12.093
It's been quite a night
at the castle. it seems.

582
01:02:13.470 --> 01:02:14.971
Yes. my lady.

583
01:02:49.797 --> 01:02:51.716
Come on. come on.

584
01:02:55.261 --> 01:02:57.805
That's it.

585
01:03:06.814 --> 01:03:07.941
Oh...

586
01:03:09.317 --> 01:03:10.444
Well done.

587
01:03:17.450 --> 01:03:19.620
- I'm sorry.
- Shh.

588
01:03:19.703 --> 01:03:22.622
- I'm sorry.
- Shh. shh. shh.

589
01:03:24.207 --> 01:03:26.125
But you wanted to know...

590
01:03:27.127 --> 01:03:29.254
if I believe it to be true.

591
01:03:31.172 --> 01:03:33.091
Believe what to be true. my King?

592
01:03:34.008 --> 01:03:35.761
Don't you remember?

593
01:03:37.471 --> 01:03:38.596
Aegon...

594
01:03:41.308 --> 01:03:42.558
Our son?

595
01:03:44.727 --> 01:03:46.270
His Dream.

596
01:03:46.854 --> 01:03:50.149
The Song of Ice... and Fi...

597
01:03:51.484 --> 01:03:53.028
It is true.

598
01:03:54.071 --> 01:03:55.988
What he saw in the North.

599
01:03:58.491 --> 01:04:00.618
The Prince That Was Promised.

600
01:04:01.703 --> 01:04:02.912
I don't understand. Viserys.

601
01:04:04.455 --> 01:04:06.040
The Prince.

602
01:04:06.124 --> 01:04:07.667
Prince Aegon?

603
01:04:08.961 --> 01:04:10.754
To unite the realm

604
01:04:10.837 --> 01:04:13.966
against the cold... and the dark.

605
01:04:17.718 --> 01:04:19.263
It is you.

606
01:04:22.015 --> 01:04:23.558
You are the one.

607
01:04:25.685 --> 01:04:27.604
You must do this.

608
01:04:29.355 --> 01:04:31.274
You must do this.

609
01:05:15.944 --> 01:05:17.863
I understand. my King.

610
01:05:38.133 --> 01:05:39.343
No more.

611
01:05:40.218 --> 01:05:41.761
No more.

612
01:06:10.749 --> 01:06:12.250
My love.

612
01:06:13.305 --> 01:07:13.472
Do you want subtitles for any video?
